text.tspan: - Smoothness from Cara malts, Carafa and English yeast,
- Heather flowers to make it candid floral,
- English style hops with both Target (Myrcene),
- 2 days dry hopping to balance out Heather flower,
- Yeast mix of English and American.
- Dry notes from Mash temperature, Brown, Black, Rye and Yeast,
- Smooth notes from CaraPils, Carafa & Muscovado,
- Complexity from Abbey, Special B, Muscovado and Yeast,
- SafAle BE-134 makes it dry with both belgian and saison notes.
- Dry notes from Brown, Black and Rye,
- A bit chocolate from Carafa and Chocolate,
- Complexity from Abbey and Special B,
- Smoothness from Cara Pils and Carafa,
- Most non-fruity hop aromas (Citrus, Spicy, Pine, Floral, Herbal)
- Elderflower to turn it even more floral instead of fruity,
- 4 days of dry hopping to give it sharp edges.
